			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Who we are:</strong></p>
<p>
Talenthouse is a fast-growing web-company that allows artists and creatives (both established and emerging) to leverage the power of social networks to make themselves better known. We lead campaigns with world-class celebrities and brands (e.g. Justin Timberlake, deadmau5, U2) that offer life changing collaboration opportunities to young, talented artists.</p>
<p>
Talenthouse is seeking dynamic and creative Russian-speaking interns looking to work in a fast paced environment. The intern should be passionate and demonstrate knowledge in various aspects of entertainment, including, but not limited to the following: Film, Photo, Fashion, Art, Design, Music.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Assist research for each Talenthouse campaign, identify and contact relevant outreach targets, build partnerships with schools and social-media influencers</li>
<li>
Develop strong partnerships with media, bloggers, online communities, universities in&nbsp;Film, Photography, Fashion, Art, Design and Music</li>
<li>
Write press releases and pitch letters, pitch media with story ideas / content</li>
<li>
Use other emerging platforms to promote our Creative campaigns, like Facebook and Twitter</li>
<li>
Analyze, review and create reports on campaign effectiveness in an effort to maximize results</li>
<li>
Write and translate articles for&nbsp;our Russian blog (including&nbsp;success stories and&nbsp;artist features)</li>
<li>
Translate&nbsp;campaigns and blog articles from English to Russian</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Russian language skills (fluent written and verbal)</li>
<li>
Self-starter able to work independently</li>
<li>
Superb attention to detail</li>
<li>
Technologically-comfortable (Microsoft Office, Google Documents)</li>
<li>
Students are welcome</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Availability:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Minimum of three days per week</li>
<li>
We are flexible regarding the work schedule and amount of hours but the more time you can commit the more responsibility you could potentially take on.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
